Sergio Osme単a was a Philippine independence leader and statesman who held several important political positions in the early 20th century. He helped gain commonwealth status for the Philippines in 1935 and served as vice president and later president from 1944 to 1946. However, he was defeated in the first election of an independent Philippines in 1946 by Manuel Roxas. Osme単a played a notable role in the struggle for Philippine independence through his work as a lawyer, editor, and politician.
